         <div>
            <head>19.3.1883 Montag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49025">Berlin</placeName> March 19. 1883 Monday.</p>
            <p>Went to <placeName key="49026">Potsdam</placeName>. We first went to <placeName key="56615">Babelsberg</placeName> where we were first shown <placeName key="56615">Babelsberg</placeName> the <persName key="8321">emperors</persName>
               palace. His bedroom is simple, with cretonne curtains the walls covered with prints.
               His writing-room is pretty but simple. After this we went to Sanssouci or Sans, souci
               as it is written over the door It was most interesting. We were first shewn <persName key="8321">Frederic the Great&#x2019;s</persName> dining room and then the room in which
               he died and his library. After some more rooms <persName key="8149">Voltaire&#x2019;s</persName> room, the walls of which are covered with animals, such as
               parrots, and squirrels which <persName key="8321">Frederic</persName> had put there
               when <persName key="8149">Voltaire</persName> was travelling and he wanted to get rid
               of him, to personnify his character. After Sanssouci we had ourselves driven to the
               new Palais. We saw the shellroom and the theater etc. etc and then came home. Went to
               the <name type="work" key="36621">Registrator auf Reisen</name>
               <note type="reg">
                  <persName key="5609">L&#x2019;Arronge</persName>
               </note> a very stupid piece in the evening</p>
         </div>
